sources.title: West of The Brazos (1950, Western) Shamrock Ellison, Lucky Hayden | Movie
sources.description:
BATTLIN’ BACK TO BACK… FOR THE RICHES OF A RANGELAND EMPIRE.
An outlaw impersonates Shamrock in order to lease his land to an oil company for $75,000.

Original title: West of The Brazos (1950) AKA: Rangeland Empire
This movie is subtitled with many language options.

Colorized version https://youtu.be/WT0Y1iqCFjw


Director: Thomas Carr
Writers: Ron Ormond, Maurice Tombragel, Robert N. Bradbury
Stars: James Ellison, Russell Hayden, Raymond Hatton, Fuzzy Knight, Julie Adams, Tom Tyler & Gene Roth
Genre: Classics, Western


00:00 Full Movie (with subtitles)
01:00 Adventure unfolds as Lucky and Shamrock encounter danger while on a mission in Wyoming.
11:28 Law enforcement officers encounter a gang led by Cyclone Kid, mistakenly attacked due to a stolen letter. They plan to track down the gang at Brazos farm.
15:22 A mysterious letter leads to a plan involving a ranch, oil company, and a doctor in a town without one.
30:31 Mystery unfolds as Shamrock Ellison searches for his mother and discovers a deceitful man claiming his identity.
31:19 Legal proceedings unfold as identities are questioned in a Western court.
36:11 Legal testimony reveals identity dispute over inheritance at Lazy Dollar Ranch.
40:47 Drama unfolds as Shamrock Ellison claims to be a police chief and a victim of identity theft and robbery.
43:27 Law enforcement officers plan to capture a suspect and prevent a potential threat in a Western setting.
47:47 Unforeseen events unfold as a group sets out to find Cyclone and his accomplice in the Wild West.
